                <div class="logic-card">
                    <h3>Logic Overview</h3>
                    <p><strong>Conceptual flow:</strong> the analyzer scores a password by combining alphabet size, length, and heuristic penalties for keyboard walks, numeric or alphabetical runs, repeated groups, dictionary fragments, and common substitutions such as <code>@</code> for <code>a</code> or <code>3</code> for <code>e</code>.</p>
                    <p><strong>Key assumptions:</strong> attackers prioritize structured guesses before pure brute force, common substitution rules are well understood, and recognizable chunks lower effective search space even when total length appears strong.</p>
